<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4612365>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 30. Characteristics of synspermia of Paradysderina fusiscuta. A: The lumen of the deferent ducts is filled with large sperm conjugates. B: Sperm conjugates are composed of four sperm, which are randomly arranged and curled around each other. C: All sperm conjugates are surrounded by a very thin secretion sheath. Numerous membranes, as well as small folds are visible in the periphery. D: Sperm are not entirely fused, thus the main sperm cell components remain surrounded by their own membrane. E: The deep implantation fossa is filled with numerous mitochondria that are arranged in a row. F: Additional mitochondria are present in the periphery of the sperm conjugate." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4612365/files/figure.png" .

